  "text": "Measurement of BP and HR. All mice were allowed 10 days of recovery from transmitter implantation surgery before any measurements were made (Fig. 1 ). This time interval is necessary for the mice to regain their circadian BP and HR rhythm [CITATION_1] . Thereafter, BP, HR, and activity responses were telemetrically recorded and stored with the Dataquest ART data acquisition system (Data Sciences International). The baseline measures were averaged over a period of 5 days before the implantation of the pump; the infusion data were collected over a period of 7 days after pump implant.",
